{{notability|date=November 2018}} The '''Association of Chamber of Commerce Executives''' is an organization for leaders of local [[Chamber of commerce|chambers of commerce]] in the United States. It was founded in 1914. ACCE's president is Mick Fleming, the author of ''Making Your Chamber Make a Difference'' and a former leader with the Business Council of New York State. The chairman of ACCE is Jay Chesshir, President & CEO of the [[Little Rock, Arkansas|Little Rock]] Regional Chamber of Commerce. The ACCE is headquartered in Alexandria, Virginia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acce.org/|title=American Chamber of Commerce Executives|access-date=28 April 2017}}</ref>
